Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Luxembourg. The Luxembourg authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus. You should comply with any additional screening measures put in place by the authorities.
Travel restrictions
Luxembourg Airport (Findel) remains open on a limited basis. Most flights are cancelled but some airlines including British Airways to London Heathrow are operating a skeleton service. Occasional flights to the UK may be available. You should consult the airline websites for further detail.
For information on how to return to the UK from Luxembourg, see Return to the UK
Other measures
The Luxembourg Government has introduced a range of recommendations and measures (in English). These measures include, but are not limited to, the closure of restaurants, caf√©s, and most non-food shops. Leisure facilities including libraries, museums and leisure centres are also closed. Sporting and cultural events have been cancelled. The public is forbidden to leave the house for social activity or to host any activity at home and are encouraged to keep movements outside their house to a minimum. Schools will be closed until 19 April.
Further advice and information is available from the Luxembourg Government (in English) and the Ministry of Health website (in French).
Further information
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
You can find more information about cases in Luxembourg on the TravelHealthPro website.
